[[Image:Doppelgelenkbus 01 KMJ.jpg|thumb|right|Large motor coach with tourists]] '''Escorted tours''' are a form of [[tourism]] in which travelers are escorted in a group to various destinations, versus a [[self-guided tour]] where the tourist is on their own.<ref>{{Citation | author1=Motorcoach Tour Mart | title=The best in escorted tours, USA and Canada via motorcoach and air | publication-date=1979 | publisher=Grace J. Talmadge and Associates | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/34614814 | accessdate=19 April 2013 }} </ref> <ref>{{Citation | title=Tours: a selection of escorted tours | journal=International Travel News | publication-date=2004-10-01 | publisher=Martin Publications, Inc | volume=29 | issue=8 | pages=94(1) | issn=0191-8761 }} </ref>
Escorted tours are also known as ''Guided tours'' or ''[[Package tour|Package Tours]]''.
Escorted tours are normally conducted by a [[Tour guide|tour]] director who takes care of all services from the beginning to end of the tour. Escorted tours also normally include the flights, hotels, [[transportation]], transfers to the [[airport]]/[[hotel]], most meals and some [[sightseeing]]. Escorted tours are often conducted by motor coach and usually no more than three nights are spent in each location visited. They are usually fast-paced and prices include most everything.
