'''Mga Kababayang Dalaga ng Malolos''' (English Translation: ''To the Young Women of Malolos'') is a letter written by [[José Rizal]] for the young women of [[Malolos]] in 1889. The letter was addressed in the time of political outrage caused by the twenty women who petitioned for a night school to study the Spanish language and be at par with men.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bangkanixiao.files.wordpress.com/2012/10/rizal-liham-sa-kababaihan-ng-malolos.pdf|title=ANG LIHAM SA MGA KADALAGAHAN SA MALOLOS, BULAKAN|last=Chua|first=Michael Charleston|date=|website=Bangka ni Xiao|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wn.com/Rizal%27s_Letter_to_the_women_of_Malolos|title=Rizal's Letter: To The Young Women of Malolos (Analysis)|last=|first=|date=|website=wn.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gmanews-tv-yahoopartner.tumblr.com/post/121894835082/podcasts-mga-akda-ni-rizal-binigyang-tinig|title=PODCASTS: Mga akda ni Rizal, binigyang-tinig|last=|first=|date=18 June 2011|website=GMANews.tv|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> 

